<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="pattern-n">pattern <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'pætn/    美 /'pætərn/  </p>
<p>[C]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>模式；方式；样式</strong></h4>
<p>the regular way in which sth happens or is done：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>changing patterns of behaviour
不断变化的行为模式</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Pay attention to the following sentence patterns. 
注意以下句型。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She has got used to the new patterns of family life.
她已经习惯了新的家庭生活方式。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>模型；纸样：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a dress pattern
连衣裙的纸样</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>图案；花样：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a pattern of dots 
点状图案</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>模范；榜样：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>set the pattern for</strong> 
为…树立典范</p></div></div>